{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blog.jetbrains.com/dotnet/2020/11/05/run-blazor-apps-within-electron-shell/\">Run Blazor Apps Within Electron Shell</a> - November 5, 2020 - This post covers how to embed Blazor into an Electron app to ship Blazor on the desktop, and how to debug our Electron application using Rider.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-10T13:47:31.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://swimburger.net/blog/dotnet/communicating-between-dotnet-and-javascript-in-blazor-with-in-browser-samples\">Communicating between .NET and JavaScript in Blazor with in-browser samples</a> - November 5, 2020 - The success of Blazor relies heavily upon how well it can integrate with the existing rich JavaScript ecosystem. The way Blazor allows you to integrate, is by enabling you to call JavaScript functions from Blazor and .NET functions from JavaScript. This is also referred to as 'JavaScript interoperability'.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-10T13:47:31.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.telerik.com/blogs/blazor-stability-testing-tools-for-bulletproof-applications\">Blazor Stability Testing Tools for Bulletproof Applications</a> - November 9, 2020 - Blazor testing may just be the biggest potential upside of the framework. Learn about the core concepts of Blazor testing that will help you make bulletproof apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-10T13:43:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Template</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sempare/sempare-delphi-template-engine\">Sempare Template Engine</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sempare/sempare-delphi-template-engine\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left: